citation: Proclamation under the Magistrates Court (Civil Division) Act 1992 (Tas)
text:
Proclamation under the Magistrates Court (Civil Division) Act 1992

I, the Governor in and over the State of Tasmania and its Dependencies in the Commonwealth of Australia, acting with the advice of the Executive Council, by this my proclamation made under section 2 of the Magistrates Court (Civil Division) Act 1992 fix 30 March 1998 as the day on which that Act commences.

30 March 1998

G. S. M. GREEN

Governor

By His Excellency's Command,

R. J. GROOM

Minister for Justice

Displayed and numbered in accordance with the Rules Publication Act 1953.

Notified in the Gazette on 30 March 1998

This proclamation is administered in the Department of Justice.
